Afghan warplanes killed 22 people ina second bombing in as many days of a remote Pakistani villagenear the Afghan border, official Radio Pakistan said.    The radio said the six planes attacked Angur Adar in theSouth Waziristan area. Afghanistan has denied previous chargesof bombing Pakistani territory.    Officials said the death toll from yesterday's Afghanbombing in Teri Mangal to the north had risen to at least 70 asmore bodies were recovered. Fifty-one people were reportedkilled yesterday. Reuter&#3;